title: SeaLink Travel Group hopes to boost tourism through $125 million acquisition
text:
SeaLink Travel Group hopes to boost t... SeaLink Travel Group hopes to boost tourism through $125 million acquisition Next Story Prev Story 2 hrs ago Read more: The Age 
Ferry and cruise operator SeaLink Travel Group will double its underlying earnings and significantly expand its tourism through the $125 million acquisition of privately held Queensland-based Transit Systems Marine and its 33 vessels. "The opportunities for those boats are more around tourism and domestic transport getting out of the resource sector," SeaLink chief executive Jeff Ellison said of the acquisition.   The Age.
